Warning Roar	SOURCEPAGE:p.45	SCHOOL:Evocation	CASTTIME:1 action	RANGE:30 feet	COMPS:V	DURATION:1 round	DESC: Menacing psychic energies transform your voice into a louder version of the natural threat of a predatory beast (such as the growl of a hunting dog, the rattle of a rattlesnake, or the roar of a lion) that is audible out to 60 feet. Choose one creature within this spell’s range, which must make an Intelligence saving throw. If the target fails, it takes 1d6 thunder damage, and until the start of your next turn it has disadvantage on the next saving throw it makes against being frightened. If that target willingly moves closer to you or attacks you before the start of your next turn, it immediately takes 1d8 psychic damage, and the spell ends. This thunder damage from this spell increases by 1d6 when you reach 5th level (2d6), 11th level (3d6), and 17th level (4d6).
							
							
							
